OL,6,FStudents have mixed opinions, some say
OL,7,Fit's difficult to adjust without being
OL,8,Fable to communicate with their
OL,9,Fparents. Others say it helps them to
OL,10,Fconcentrate and addresses phone
OL,11,Faddiction.
OL,13,FLabour Councillor Emma Daniel said,
OL,14,F''We can't force parents to make this
OL,15,Fdecision. All I can tell you is, I
OL,16,Fthink it's dangerous for your
OL,17,Fchildren, teachers think it's
OL,18,Fdangerous for your children, social
OL,19,Fworkers are dealing with the harm
OL,20,Fwhere children have been coerced to do
OL,21,Fthings that they don't want to do.
